he Nautilus system admins team has rolled out a web UI application for their backup utility on the Nautilus backup server within the Stratos Datacenter. This application operates on port 5002, and firewalld is active on the server. To meet operational needs, the following requirements have been identified:



Allow all incoming connections on port 5002/tcp. Ensure the zone is set to public.

Ans:-

o allow incoming connections on port 5002/tcp and ensure the zone is set to public, you can follow these steps:

Open the terminal on the Nautilus backup server.

Check the current zone:

firewall-cmd --get-active-zones
This command will show you the active zones. Ensure that the zone is set to public.

Allow incoming connections on port 5002/tcp:

firewall-cmd --zone=public --add-port=5002/tcp --permanent
Reload the firewall to apply the changes:

firewall-cmd --reload
These commands will configure the firewall to allow incoming connections on port 5002/tcp and ensure the zone is set to public. 
